Class DoubleDouble

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jagg.DoubleDouble
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<DoubleDouble>

    public class DoubleDouble
extends Object
implements Comparable<DoubleDouble>
    A DoubleDouble is used when extra precision is necessary to cut way down on floating point errors.
    Since:
    0.4.0
    Author:
    Randy Gettman
